title: [LLM Runtime] Enable GPTQ models
body:
## Type of Change

feature

## Description

detail description 
JIRA ticket: [NLPTOOLKIU-931](https://jira.devtools.intel.com/browse/NLPTOOLKIU-931)

Support GPTQ model in llm runtime.

- [x] parse GPTQ model from inc
- [x] parse GPTQ model from huggingface
- [x] convert bloom GPTQ to q4_0
- [x] convert hugging face llama to q4_0
- convert to jblas will be done in next stage

## Expected Behavior & Potential Risk

```python
from transformers import AutoTokenizer, TextStreamer
from intel_extension_for_transformers.transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, WeightOnlyQuantConfig

model_name = "/mnt/disk1/data2/zhenweil/models/gptq/Llama-2-7B-Chat-GPTQ"  # or local path to model
woq_config = WeightOnlyQuantConfig(from_gptq=True, use_cache=True)
prompt = "Once upon a time, a little girl"

tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name, trust_remote_code=True)
inputs = tokenizer(prompt, return_tensors="pt").input_ids
streamer = TextStreamer(tokenizer)
model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(model_name, quantization_config=woq_config, trust_remote_code=True)

while True:
    prompt = input("> ").strip()
    if prompt == "quit":
        break
    b_prompt = "[INST]{}[/INST]".format(prompt)  # prompt template for llama2
    inputs = tokenizer(b_prompt, return_tensors="pt").input_ids
    outputs = model.generate(inputs, streamer=streamer, interactive=True, ignore_prompt=True, do_sample=True)

```

![image](https://github.com/intel/intel-extension-for-transformers/assets/109187816/c0c5e02f-e270-4f0e-af8f-3d10aa03aa3a)


## How has this PR been tested?

N/A

N/A

Per-model changes: - `n_ctx` is now a field of `model_context` rathe then model class themselves, together with the added `n_keep` and `shift_roped_k`. It is also more semantic as `n_ctx` is read from args rather than model files. - Added an extra argument `n_total` for `xxx_model_eval_internal`, which provides the number of tokens evaluated so far (including evicted tokens if there is any). Note: `n_past` is used as the offset to which the KV is cached to even before this PR - in `xxx_utils.cpp`, the template argument of the `unique_ptr` in `model_load_internal` are corrected to the derived classes - Time are calculated outside of the `xxx_utils.cpp` Note: The version for fused-attention will be implemented in a later PR ## Expected Behavior & Potential Risk N/A ## How has this PR been tested?

title: [NeuralChat] Support optimization for server mode and add ut cases
body:
## Type of Change

feature
API not changed

## Description

Support different optimizations for server mode and add ut cases.

# ipex int8 optimization
optimization:
    ipex_int8: True

# itrex int4 llm runtime optimization
optimization:
    use_llm_runtime: true
    optimization_type: "weight_only"
    compute_dtype: "int8"
    weight_dtype: "int4"

# itrex int4 optimization
optimization:
    use_llm_runtime: false
    optimization_type: "weight_only"
    compute_dtype: "int8"
    weight_dtype: "int4"

# mix precision bf16
optimization:
    optimization_type: "mix_precision"
    mix_precision_dtype: "bf16"

# bits and bytes
optimization:
    optimization_type: "bits_and_bytes"
    load_in_4bit: True
    bnb_4bit_quant_type: 'nf4'
    bnb_4bit_use_double_quant: True
    bnb_4bit_compute_dtype: "bfloat16"

Users can use different optimization methods on server deployment.
